  "texts": [
    "When the temperature is set to 0, the token with the highest probability is always chosen.",
    "As the temperature value increases, less likely tokens also have a chance to be selected.",
    "In the OpenAI API documentation, it is explicitly stated: \"Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic\" [54].",
    "For the purposes of our experiment, we selected three temperature values to explore how the model's properties change depending on this crucial parameter.",
    "The first value is chosen as zero, representing deterministic selection of the most probable token."
  ],
